Undersheriff Tim Albin, of Tulsa County, Oklahoma, quit his job Monday after new revelations about how the department treated elderly killer Robert Bates .
Bates, 73, accidentally grabbed his pistol and fatally shot Eric Harris, 44, after he was tackled to the ground .
Video of the killing shows Bates exclaiming that he opened fired by accident, and apologizing for his actions .
He has been charged with manslaughter - but a judge allowed him to take a month-long holiday to the Bahamas .